How to improve instance segmentation AP metrics with human knowledge.

\subsection{Likelihood Function} \label{sec:lf}

A \emph{likelihood function} $L$ represents the belief of instance segmentation accuracy $A$ based on the human opinion $H$.
In order to build the LF, the annotated ground truth of $H$ is required.
Therefore, $H$ can be represented as a binary ground truth mask $H_{GT}=\{h_{GT}(x^{\text{i}}),h_{GT}(x^{\text{j}}),\cdots,h_{GT}(x^{\text{N}})\}$, where $h_{GT}(x^{\text{i}})=1\Leftrightarrow h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})=1$. In addition, $h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})$ is calculated by Eq.~\ref{eq:H} in Section.~\ref{sec:Hv}.
The overall likelihood function $L=\prod_{i=1}^{N}L(h_{v}(x^{\text{i}}))$ is then a summation of single mask $h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})$ and can be formulated as
\begin{equation}
L(h_{v}(x^{\text{i}}))=\left\{\begin{aligned}
p\big(h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})\big) \cdot h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})
\quad\big\lvert\big.\,h_{v}(x^{\text{i}}) = 1\big\rvert,\\
p\big(h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})\big) \cdot (1-h_{v}(x^{\text{i}}) )
\qquad\big\lvert\big.\,h_{v}(x^{\text{i}}) = 0\big\rvert.
\end{aligned}\right.
\label{eq:Lhv}
\end{equation}

As mentioned previously, the human opinion dataset $H$ is a binary mask with 1 (green) and 0 (blue) denoting \textit{correct} instances and \textit{incorrect} instances. Therefore, a likelihood function $L$ can be viewed as a mask for instance segmentation prediction. The mask can be calculated from $H$ using the Eq.~\ref{eq:Lhv}. As shown in $H$, the value of instance segmentation accuracy $A$ can be estimated more precisely in the range [0.0,1.0].
When $h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})$ takes a value of 1, then $L$ will be a mask with high density value, which means the corresponding instance segmentation classification is confident (Figs.~\ref{fig:hv} and~\ref{fig:dL}). When $h_{v}(x^{\text{i}})$ takes a value of 0, then $L$ will be a mask with low density value, which indicates the corresponding instance segmentation classification is uncertain.
Therefore, according to the human opinion $H$, the current predictive model can be updated by optimizing the network parameters $\theta$ using a new mask $L$. The mask $L$ can be further normalized to a scalar value between -1 to 1.

\textbf{Improved Instance Segmentation Model}: The improved predictive model is then obtained by
\begin{equation}
\begin{aligned}
\hat{A}=&\max_{\theta} \ L \bigg(\big\langle(\bm{\varphi}^{(i)},h^{(i)})\big\rangle\bigg)
\\=&\max_{\theta} \{\underbrace{L(\langle\bm{\varphi}^{(i)}, h^{(i)}\rangle)}_{\text{normalized}} \},
\end{aligned}
\label{eq:norma}
\end{equation}
\begin{figure}
\includegraphics[width=\columnwidth]{figures/instance_image_cropped.pdf}
\caption{An instance segmentation confidence mask predicted from an annotated instance segmentation dataset: (a) is incorrect, (b) is correct.
}
\label{fig:hv}
\end{figure}
