what does the @ in python do.

Answer: `@` allows you to decorate functions or methods in Python. In your case you want to decorate the `add` method. See the [documentation](https://docs.python.org/3/reference/decorator.html).

\begin{code}
@add()
def __add__(self):
    return self.x, self.y
\end{code}

Answer: \begin{code}
def __add__(self, y):
    return self.x + y
\end{code}

