Answer: You need to add decorations to specific methods, e.g. the [add] method.

You can use the [decorators](http://learnpythonthehardway.org/book/ex6.html#ex6-1-decorator) to do so.

Let say you want to add 5 to the current value of the variable, and let say you named the variable `somevar`

\begin{code}
@add(5)
def somevar():
    return 5

print(somevar())       # -> 5
print(somevar())       # -> 10
\end{code}

