Answer: Your code is in C. Take "18 is less than 20" as example. To know that, you should understand the logic of this comparison.

From the "18 is less than 20", we know that 18 is less than 20;

In C, this logic is,

\begin{code}
if (18 < 20) {
    printf ("18 is less than 20");
}
\end{code}

Thus, "18 is less than 20" is not correct.

In fact,

\begin{code}
if (18 < 20) {
    printf ("18 is less than 20");
} else if (18 < 20) { // here, the code after else if will not run
    printf ("18 is less than 20"); // error, "else if" should be "else", thus, 18 is not less than 20.
} else {
    printf ("18 is less than 20"); // error, "else" should be "switch", so 18 is less than 20.
}
